Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with sign language translation, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is highly likely to belong to this category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - Sign language involves visual gestures, and the paper uses videos to learn tokens. Hence, it is also likely to belong to this category.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses various machine learning techniques such as adversarial, multitask, and transfer learning to improve tokenization. Therefore, it is likely to belong to this category.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with developing a system that can translate sign language, which involves artificial intelligence techniques. Hence, it is also likely to belong to this category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses videos as input data, and the output is also in the form of videos. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to this category.
